نام", "in_corpus": true, "count": 10, "asp": "i", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "s"}, {"role": "present_1mp", "form": "نَنام", "in_corpus": true, "count": 1, "asp": "i", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "p"}, {"role": "past_1mp", "form": "نِمْنا", "in_corpus": false, "count": null, "asp": "p", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "p"}, {"role": "past_1ms", "form": "نِمْتُ", "in_corpus": true, "count": 2, "asp": "p", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "s"}], "frequency_in_corpus": 114, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "أَنام", "root": "أنم", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 1}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 10}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": [""], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%85"}}, "translations": {"en": "to sleep", "fa": "خوابیدن", "ur": "سونا", "tr": "uyumak", "id": "tidur", "bn": "ঘুমানো", "es": "dormir", "fr": "dormir", "de": "schlafen", "ru": "спать", "zh": "睡觉"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to sleep", "examples": [{"text": "الطِّفْلُ نَامَ بِسُكُونٍ بَعْدَ يَوْمٍ طَوِيلٍ.", "english": "The child slept peacefully after a long day."}]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to go to bed"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to go to sleep", "examples": [{"text": "أنَامْ أَوْ أَقْرَءْ.", "english": "I go to sleep or read."}]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to abate, to subside, to let up, to calm down"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be inactive, to be listless"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be numb"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to neglect, to omit, to overlook"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to forget"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to accept, to assent to, to acquiesce in"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to trust, to have confidence in"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Cognate with Hebrew נָם (nɔm)."}, "ipa": ["/naː.ma/"], "lanes_definition": null, "classical_definitions": {"source": "hawramani", "url": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%85/", "headword_ar": "نام", "entries": [{"lexicon_id": "dictionary_49", "lexicon_en": "Arabic-English Lexicon by Edward William Lane (d. 1876)", "lexicon_ar": "المعجم العربي الإنجليزي لإدوارد وليام لين", "permalink": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=131799#b1ebc6", "body_html": "<h3>نام</h3><span class=\"sense\">1</span> نَامَتْ رِجْلُهُ (assumed <abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">I. q.</abbr> خَدِرَتْ [His leg, or foot, became benumbed, or torpid]. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr> in art. بسر.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> نَامَ (assumed <abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) It (a woman's anklet) ceased to sound, by reason of the fulness of the leg: like as one says [in the <abbr title=\"contrary\">contr.</abbr> case], استيقظ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr> in art. يقظ.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> نَامَ has for its <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. ns</abbr>. نَوْمٌ and مَنَامٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b4:</span> نَامَ الثَّوْبُ <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> رَقَدَ [<abbr title=\"quod vide (i.e. on this [matter], go see...)\">q. v.</abbr>] (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, art. رقد.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b5:</span> نَامَتِ السُّوقُ <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> رَقَدَت [<abbr title=\"quod vide (i.e. on this [matter], go see...)\">q. v.</abbr>] (<abbr title=\"Thaʿlab, author of the Faṣīḥ\">Th</abbr>, in <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>, art. رقد.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b6:</span> نَامَ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) He lay; as opposed to he sat and he stood. See نَائِمٌ. <span class=\"sub-sense\">b7:</span> نَامَ عَنْ حَاجَتِهِ He cared not for the object of his want, neglected it. (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) 2 نَوَّمَ and ↓ أَنَامَ (assumed <abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) It benumbed, or torpified: see نَامَتْ رِجْلُهُ.<span class=\"sense\">3</span> نَاوَمْتُهُ فِى شِعَارٍ وَاحِدٍ [I slept with him in one under-garment]. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, art. شعر.) 4 أَنْاَمَ see 2.<span class=\"sense\">10</span> اِسْتَنَامَ إِليْهِ He trusted to him, and became quiet, or easy, in mind; relied upon him. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) اِمْرَأَةٌ نَؤُومُ الضُّحَى <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> رَقُودُ الضحى [which see]. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, art. رقد.) نَائِمٌ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) Lying; as opposed to sitting and standing. (<abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>.) أَنْوَمُ [More, or most, prone to sleep]. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, art. فهد.) مَنَامٌ Time of sleep. (<abbr title=\"Tafsīr al-Jalālayn by al-Suyūṭī\">Jel</abbr>, xxxix. 43.) See also 1."}]}, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}